{
  "texts": [
    "Although the universities gave staff free rein, the responsibilities suddenly shifted from the university to the teachers, who are not likely to be familiar with this new technology.Phase one ended when a student in CUHK was reported to have gotten caught using ChatGPT to do a course assignment on 11 March [25], the concerned student claimed that he wrote the essay by himself and only used ChatGPT to look up information, thus argued that the university had not prohibited the use of ChatGPT at the time when he submitted the assignment.",
    "In reporting the incident, the course lecturer said he was only able to give a low grade to the student based on the assignment's quality since there was no clear university policy on the use of ChatGPT at that time.",
    "Apart from policy loopholes, the \"penalty\" was light because the case was not being treated as academic honesty or plagiarism at the time.",
    "This resulted because there is no guideline regarding what is the proper use of ChatGPT for academic assignments, so he failed to take the matter any further.",
    "This highlights the importance of timely university policy to prevent grey areas in handling misuse of AI-generated technology in general."
  ]
}